MAV is the national train network in Hungary.
I contacted them to obtain their GTFS data, then contacted Navitia for them to add it. 
Their Data team is actually working on it. (CF : https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/navitia/22umWYkZq-4)

@schildbach If I can, I will make a PR into public-transport-enabler once available on Navitia.
@grote Can you leave the issue open until then ?

Anyway, I'll let you know about any progress on this topic.

Version: 1.1.7

When going to ‚ÄòNearby Stations‚Äô from the side menu and selecting ‚ÄòUse Current Position‚Äô, GPS is activated, and the location box is updated with the current GPS position. Network requests are then made, but the results are not shown on the screen.

This appears to be due to the following line in `NearbyStationsFragment`, since `deactivateGPS` is called from `LocationGpsView` when the GPS lookup completes:

```java
LocationGpsView.LocationGpsListener listener = new LocationGpsView.LocationGpsListener() {
	...
	@Override
	public void deactivateGPS() { ui.stations_area.setVisibility(GONE); }
```

Removing this statement fixes the issue and results are shown as expected.

Please remove from translation (from transifex) names of transport companies, which of course shouldn't be translated:
- WIENER LINIEN (176) - here even name of the city (Wien) is swapped with name of company, so string (236) should be "Wien" (not-capitalized);
- Deutsche Bahn (231);
- MTA, CDTA, Port Authority, Staten Island Ferry, NFTA, Rockland County, Rochester-Genesee Regional Transportation Authority (222) - this provider seems to be inactive;
- SPTRANS EPTC (239).

String "FR-SW" (241) looks strange, maybe it should be changed to "South-Western France"?
